Product name: Muffy VanderBear Collectible Teddy Clawed Monet / Gilbearny Collection North American Bear Company / Lavender Purple / Artist Bear
Description:
Sweet lavender collectible bear.  In the spring of 1984, Muffy VanderBear came to life as the fifth and littlest (7" tall) member of the VanderBear Family.  This Muffy, named "Clawed Monet," is from the Gibearny Collection (celebrating the romantic lavender-hues in Monet's Water Lily paintings of the French gardens at Gibearny), which was introduced in the Spring of 1990 and retired in 1994.  
Muffy is wearing a lovely dress in a floral print on soft gray, a lavender painter's smock and lavender vinyl shoes.  She has a  white flower and bow on her head, carries a painter's palette and has a tube of paint in her pocket.
Made by the North American Bear Company, Muffy is fully-jointed with a hand-stitched nose and rich golden plush.  The VanderBears are classic collectors' bears. In addition to baby Muffy, the VanderBear family includes father Cornelius (20" tall), mother Alice (18" tall), brother Fuzzy (12" tall), and sister Fluffy (12" tall).
No box.  Mint condition with original hang tags; factory dressed.  Designed by Barbara Isenberg.  Costume by Odl Bauer.  Ships via USPS Priority Mail Medium Box.

Description:
This listing is for a CUSTOM ORDER fleece pet bed -  NOT A READY TO SHIP ITEM.  I made the pictured pet beds as a special request for a customer, and I decided to make a listing for custom pet beds.  The pictured beds were made for a dog, but I can also make the beds for cats using cat print fleece.  
The bed is made with soft fleece; printed fleece on the top and solid color fleece on the bottom.  In between the two fleece layers is a layer of 1/2 inch thick quilt batting.  The bed is sewn all around the edges and then three inches from the sides.  The sides of the mat are stuffed with polyester fiberfill and are higher than the center of the bed.  The sides are stuffed very tightly and will keep their shape.  
As the bed is a custom, it will be made to order, and you can choose your fabric.  If you give me an idea of the type of print or color you would like, I will send you pictures of sample fabrics.  Once all the details are worked out, I will send you a custom order listing.  Once the order is paid for, I will order the fabric and start on your order when the fabric comes in.  Completion time is approximately 3 weeks.
Two sizes are pictured:
small:  approximately 23 long (vertical) x 14 wide (horizontal)
(Picture 4) Compared to large size in picture 5.
large:  approximately 24 wide (horizontal) x 30 long (vertical)
(Pictures 1 - 3) Compared to small size in picture 5.
The bed is washable on cold water, gentle cycle, no fabric softener and tumble dry low heat.  
Any questions, please let me know.  I would be happy to work with you to make the perfect mat for your pet.
Thanks for visiting, and have a nice day.

Product name: Large Nautical Boat Photography, Rowboat Dory Oars Rope Photo, Oversize Vertical Wall Art, Coastal Beach Artwork, Teal Navy Blue Beige White
Description:
Featured on Apartment Therapy, February 2016!
Fine art photograph of a classic, blue rowboat tied up in Bristol Harbor in Bristol, Rhode Island. 
TITLE: Room for Two
 
* This limited edition photo will be printed with archival pigmented inks, on your choice of either fine art, Hahnemuhle Photo Rag Ultra Smooth paper, or Kodak Endura Lustre paper. 
Hahnemuhle Photo Rag Ultra Smooth is an archival, heavyweight museum-quality paper with a completely matte, smooth finish. This is a premium fine art paper which provides the ultimate longevity and quality of print. The matte surface of this paper eliminates the possibility of glare under direct lighting.
Kodak Endura Lustre paper is a semi-matte, professional photo paper which provides excellent saturation and tones. The availability of this paper makes it a more economical option, and also allows for larger print sizes. Lustre paper is a hybrid between glossy and matte, giving the saturation and richness of a glossy paper, without the shine.
* The print will be hand-signed and dated in the lower corner or back of the piece, with the edition number hand-written in the opposite corner. The print run for this piece is 50 copies.
* All prints will be packaged in acid-free, moisture resistant sleeves, and shipped in stiff cardboard mailers, to ensure they arrive in perfect condition.

Description:
This wedding knife has been perfectly engineered with a long handle to allow both partners' hands to have a spot to hold. Further, its thinner blade achieves an ideal cut through cake, ice cream, fruit, pie and more! This wedding cake knife is lovely for a rustic wedding, as a wedding gift or bridal shower gift for bride. After your perfect day, use this cake cutter in your kitchen every day for cutting cheese, fruit or spreading jam on toast.
Your initials or custom phrase (I wrote "best day ever" in cursive on this one) will be lovingly hand-burned into the side of this tool. 
This utensil, designed in collaboration with Elzner Originals, is made from Canadian cherry wood in Ontario and is exclusive to Lace and Twig...this beautiful knife makes a very durable kitchen tool. Further, wood has antibacterial properties making this a safe and eco choice for your wedding and home. 
This knife has been rubbed in olive oil and does not require special maintenance, apart from using soap and water to wash and re-oiling every once in while. Use this on ceramic, teflon, etc...it will not harm your beautiful pots, pans or silver stand.
Please do not put this in the dishwasher...wood dries out and it loses its smooth "skin." Use camping rules...a little bit of soap and water and it will be ready for the next cake :)

How its made by me. Step by Step Process
 
All of my products are made by me and only me.
1. Each of these unique items are first designed in CAD ( computer design) by me. 
2.After I have done the 3D design on my computer we will print the design in wax. 
3.After the design has been printed in wax I will then cast it into the metal of your choice which can be white, yellow or rose gold. 14k or 18k which ever you would prefer. 
4.After the casting has been done I will polish the ring to clean up any excess gold and mold it into the perfect ring. 
5.The next day I will start drilling into the metal so I can start setting the diamonds into the ring. 6.Once the diamonds have been set into the ring, I will then start to polish it up and then add the center stone if needed. 
7.Once all the diamonds have been set I will re-polish the ring again to perfect it. Once all these steps have been accomplished I will dip it in German Rhodium and hand it or ship it over to you.

Product name: Chinese Rice Paper Umbrella
Description:
This is a colorful and cheerful hand painted Chinese oil paper umbrella. It is in good condition, but does have some some issues. Three wood supports have come loose from the string that holds them in place, which can easily be fixed. There are a few small pokes in the rice paper due to these being loose. It is in good working condition and pops up and folds down easily. Umbrellas like these can add color to a room on top of wardrobes or tall chests of drawers. This one is especially pretty with it's hand painted flowers.
Oil paper umbrellas originated in China, but have been a part of many Asian cultures since. They had many uses and significances over the years.  In wedding ceremonies the Matron of Honor would shield the bride upon arrival to ward of evil spirits and given as a wedding gift would signify blessing to the woman to have a son. It was also used in traditional Japanese dances and tea ceremonies and as gifts to coming of age16 year old boys . 
This umbrella measures nearly 22 inches long and when open is about 33 inches wide.
If you have any questions or would like more pictures, please message me.
